  "narrative": "DRIVER\nCHF leads D1 CSM at 100 but is the most critical divergence alert: H4 CSM has collapsed to 32, a 68-point drop that overrides the D1 narrative and signals CHF is actively fading intraday. GBPCHF and USDCHF are the primary expression vehicles \u2014 USDCHF correlation with EURUSD at -0.82 means EUR weakness amplifies CHF selling pressure, while GBPUSD H4 CSM surge to 100 with GBPJPY correlated at +0.93 makes GBPCHF the cleanest long setup on current flow.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: GBPUSD CMP 50 with H4 at 63 rising sharply, GBPJPY H4 at 66 rising sharply, NZDUSD H4 at 57 rising\nFading: CADJPY CMP 45 with D1 at 31 flat, USDCHF CMP 44 with H4 at 42 fading\n\nWATCH\nIran de-escalation follow-through drives WTI below 100, hitting CADJPY directly lower given CAD oil linkage and CADJPY D1 CSM at zero\nChina stimulus headlines extend copper gains above 6.40, validating AUDJPY D1 plus H4 strong buy alignment for continuation long\nUS 10Y yield steepening at 4.623 against falling 2Y pressures USD further, accelerating EURUSD H4 momentum from 55 upward",
